<P><H1 align=center>ADD/EDIT MORTGAGE RELATED LIFE POLICIES – DC101</H1>
<P></P>
<P><FONT color=red>NOTE: fields shown in red are mandatory 
and must be completed to proceed</FONT>            </P>
<P>This screen is used to collect details of any life policies that are linked 
to the mortgage, either to provide cover in the event of premature death or to 
repay the mortgage debt at the end of the term. All details should be provided 
by the policyholder.</P>
<P><H3>Life Policy Owner: </H3>Select the name of the 
policyholder from the drop down list. If it is a sole application, the name will 
be pre-completed for you.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Policy Number: </H3>Input the policy number, which will 
be shown on the policy document.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Policy Type: </H3>Select the type of policy from the 
drop down list.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Monthly Premium: </H3>Input the total monthly premium 
paid on the policy selected.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Year of Maturity: </H3>Input the date the policy is due 
to mature/expire as set out in the policy details.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Minimum Death Benefit: </H3>Input the minimum amount 
payable by the Life Company in the event of death of the policyholder. This will 
be specified on the policy.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Maturity Value: </H3>If the policy is of a type that 
pays a maturity value at the end of it’s term, such as an Endowment Policy, 
input the amount estimated on the policy.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Is the policy to be assigned to the new loan: </H3>Click the YES radio button if the policy is being used to repay part or all 
of the mortgage balance. An assigned policy will be physically held by the 
lender, and the proceeds paid directly to them at maturity.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Is this a new policy: </H3>Click the YES radio button 
if the policy is newly taken out.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Are you the Life Assured: </H3>Is the applicant the 
named life assured on the policy.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Are there any additional policyholders: </H3>Click YES 
if the policy is in more than one name, then add the additional persons details 
in the box provided.
<P></P>
<P><H3>Life Office: </H3>
<P>Input the name of the life company, and click on the Directory Search button. 
This will take you to a screen where you need to input the name, town and post 
code of the company. Then select from the Filter drop down list whether you want 
to search for the Head Office address or another.</P>
<P>Click on the Directory Search button, and the system will search for the 
address of the company specified. Highlight the correct address from the search 
box and click Select. This will take you back to the main screen where the 
address details will be populated for you.</P>
<P>If the address is not held in the directory, input the post code and search 
for the address by clicking the PAF Search button. Select the address required 
from the list provided. If the address is still not found, input manually in the 
fields provided.</P>
<P>Click the Add to Directory button if you wish to add the name and address of 
the company to the directory.</P>
<P></P>
<P><H3>Another: </H3>If the applicants have more than one 
policy, click the ‘Another’ button when all details of the policy are completed. 
You will then be able to complete the above fields for the new policy.
<P></P>
<P><H3>OK: </H3>When all policy details have been completed, 
click the ‘OK’ button toreturn to the previous screen.
<P></P>
 
